                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A manuscript scroll with text in both kanbun and katakana-majiri including coloured diagrams of the human body with acupuncture points and some internal organs named, copied in the first half of 19th century. According to the notes in English accompanying this item, it was executed by Yoshida Ikiu in 1688 and was formerly property of the Yoshida family (1500-1910), but there is no evidence to support any of these claims. </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="js" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_100">

                            <textLang otherLangs="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                                <title type="original" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">十四経五蔵六府</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Jūshikei gozō roppu</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="en" source="IANA">The fourteen meridians, the five viscera and the six bowels</title>                                           
                            
                            <note>The title is a descriptive title given by the cataloguer for the purposes of identification. The title given on the wooden box lid is 十四経絡之図 and internally 禁灸之部、禁鍼之部.</note>
                            <note>十四経五蔵六府（尾題）。 箱題「十四経絡之図」、内題「禁灸之部、禁鍼之部」。図中に「天道」「針殺」などと題する文章あり。</note>
                            
